This paper is most likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it describes the development of an NLP assistant for a collaborative development environment. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of semantic graphs and coreference chains, which are common NLP techniques. 

The paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as NLP is a subfield of AI. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper mentions the use of a logic programming library to create an NLP database, which could involve machine learning techniques. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper mentions the use of queries to mine triples from the NLP database. 

Finally, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible sub-category as the paper describes the development of an NLP assistant for a collaborative development environment.
